-124031400657_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Simultaneous%20Polls%3A%20Kovind%20Panel%20Lays%20Down%20Synchronisation%20of%20Terms%2C%20Cutting%20Short%20Assembly%20Tenures%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26110403%2FThe-Wire-56.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Union%20government-appointed%20high-level%20committee%20headed%20by%20former%20President%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20submitted%20its%20report%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%20proposal%20on%20Thursday%20(March%2014)%2C%20recommending%20simultaneous%20polls%20in%20the%20country%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20assemblies%20as%20well%20as%20local%20bodies%20(including%20panchayats%20and%20municipalities).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%2018%2C626-page%20report%2C%20submitted%20to%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20recommended%20the%20conduct%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20in%20two%20steps.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20step%2C%20simultaneous%20elections%20will%20be%20held%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20state%20assemblies%20and%20in%20the%20second%2C%20elections%20will%20be%20held%20to%20the%20municipalities%20and%20panchayat%20bodies%20within%20100%20days%20of%20the%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20state%20assemblies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20has%20recommended%20inserting%20Article%2082A%20in%20the%20constitution%20in%20order%20to%20synchronise%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20state%20assemblies%20and%20cutting%20short%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20terms%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20in%20the%20synchronisation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20has%20said%20that%20the%20discontinuation%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20in%20the%20country%2C%20two%20decades%20after%20independence%2C%20has%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbaneful%20effect%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20polity%20and%20society.%20Initially%2C%20two%20elections%20were%20held%20every%20ten%20years%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20several%20elections%20are%20being%20held%20every%20year.%20This%20casts%20a%20huge%20burden%20on%20the%20government%2C%20businesses%2C%20workers%2C%20courts%2C%20political%20parties%2C%20candidates%20contesting%20elections%2C%20and%20civil%20society%20at%20large.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20that%20the%20government%20must%20develop%20a%20legally%20tenable%20mechanism%20in%20order%20to%20restore%20the%20cycle%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20under%20Kovind%20was%20set%20up%20on%20September%202%2C%202023%20and%20includes%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20former%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20former%20finance%20commission%20chairperson%20N.K.%20Singh%2C%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary-general%20Subhash%20C.%20Kashyap%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%20and%20former%20chief%20vigilance%20commissioner%20Sanjay%20Kothari.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20was%20compiled%20after%20taking%20responses%20from%2047%20political%20parties%2C%20of%20which%2015%20opposed%20the%20exercise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20responses%20were%20also%20sought%20from%20four%20former%20chief%20justices%20of%20India%2C%20former%20chief%20justices%20of%20high%20courts%2C%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%20and%20the%20stakeholders%20of%20apex%20business%20organisations%20like%20the%20ASSOCHAM%2C%20FICCI%2C%20and%20CII.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResponses%20were%20also%20sought%20from%20the%20general%20public.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EState%20assembly%20terms%20to%20be%20cut%20short%20to%20synchronise%20simultaneous%20polls%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20has%20recommended%20that%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20in%20the%20synchronisation%20of%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%2C%20the%20president%20may%20bring%20in%20a%20notification%2C%20issued%20on%20the%20date%20of%20the%20first%20sitting%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9CAppointed%20date%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20recommended%20cutting%20short%20the%20tenure%20of%20those%20state%20assemblies%20that%20are%20constituted%20after%20this%20appointed%20date%20and%20before%20the%20expiry%20of%20the%20full%20term%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20the%20tenure%20of%20all%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20constituted%20by%20elections%20to%20the%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20after%20the%20appointed%20date%20and%20before%20the%20expiry%20of%20the%20full%20term%20of%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%2C%20shall%20be%20only%20for%20the%20period%20ending%20up%20to%20the%20subsequent%20general%20elections%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThereafter%2C%20all%20general%20elections%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20and%20all%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20shall%20be%20held%20together%20simultaneously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20implies%20that%20if%20the%20notification%20is%20issued%20after%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20June%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20then%20all%20those%20states%20in%20which%20assembly%20elections%20are%20due%20to%20be%20held%20in%20subsequent%20years%20before%202029%2C%20will%20be%20cut%20short.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20could%20include%20states%20like%20Maharashtra%20and%20Haryana%2C%20where%20elections%20are%20due%20later%20this%20year%3B%20Delhi%20and%20Bihar%2C%20where%20elections%20are%20due%20in%202025%3B%20followed%20by%20other%20states%20like%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Assam%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20in%202026%3B%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20in%202027%3B%20and%20Meghalaya%2C%20Nagaland%2C%20Tripura%20and%20Karnataka%20in%202028.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20has%20recommended%20an%20%E2%80%98implementation%20group%E2%80%99%20to%20be%20constituted%20to%20look%20into%20the%20execution%20of%20the%20recommendations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESynchronisation%20of%20municipal%20and%20panchayat%20elections%20with%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assembly%20polls%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20order%20to%20conduct%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20municipal%20and%20panchayat%20bodies%20along%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20recommended%20the%20introduction%20of%20Article%20324A%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20also%20recommended%20an%20amendment%20in%20Article%20325%20for%20enabling%20a%20single%20electoral%20roll%20and%20single%20elector%E2%80%99s%20photo%20identity%20cards%2C%20which%20will%20be%20prepared%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20state%20election%20commissions%2C%20which%20will%20substitute%20any%20other%20electoral%20roll%20prepared%20by%20the%20ECI.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20this%20will%20require%20ratification%20by%20states%20(with%20a%20one-third%20majority).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EImplementation%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%20will%20not%20require%20such%20ratification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20these%20amendments%20touch%20upon%20State%20subjects%20(Entry%205)%20of%20Schedule%20VII%2C%20Part%20IX%2C%20and%20Part%20IX%20A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20ratification%20by%20the%20States%20will%20be%20required%20under%20Article%20368(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20implementing%20step%20one%2C%20which%20is%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20House%20of%20the%20People%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20does%20not%20necessitate%20ratification%20by%20the%20states.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHung%20house%20and%20no-confidence%20motions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20has%20recommended%20that%20fresh%20elections%20be%20held%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20hung%20house%20or%20a%20no-confidence%20motion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20such%20fresh%20elections%20are%20held%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20then%20the%20new%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20only%20serve%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20preceding%20House%E2%80%99s%20term.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20this%20remainder%20period%20ends%2C%20the%20new%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20be%20considered%20dissolved%2C%20the%20committee%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20fresh%20elections%20are%20held%20to%20state%20assemblies%2C%20then%20the%20new%20assembly%2C%20unless%20sooner%20dissolved%2C%20will%20continue%20till%20the%20end%20of%20the%20full%20term%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Bill%20will%20have%20to%20be%20introduced%20in%20the%20Parliament%20amending%20Article%2083%20(Duration%20of%20Houses%20of%20Parliament)%20and%20Article%20172%20(Duration%20of%20State%20Legislatures).%20This%20Constitutional%20Amendment%20will%20not%20need%20ratification%20by%20the%20States%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20one%20of%20its%20members%2C%20Kashyap%2C%20had%20recommended%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconstructive%20vote%20of%20no-confidence%E2%80%9D%20as%20in%20Germany%2C%20where%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20motion%20of%20no%20confidence%20against%20a%20government%2C%20a%20positive%20vote%20of%20confidence%20in%20an%20alternate%20leader%20or%20government%20is%20required.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20suggestion%20was%20not%20taken%20by%20the%20committee%2C%20which%20said%20in%20the%20report%20that%20the%20prevailing%20parliamentary%20practice%20need%20not%20be%20changed%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMaking%20a%20motion%20of%20no%20confidence%20by%20the%20Members%20of%20the%20Parliament%20is%20not%20only%20their%20right%2C%20but%20also%20their%20responsibility.%20The%20committee%20would%20not%20like%20to%20dilute%20this%20feature%20of%20the%20Indian%20parliamentary%20system%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFifteen%20parties%20opposed%20simultaneous%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20it%20had%20received%20responses%20from%2047%20political%20parties%2C%20of%20which%2015%20opposed%20simultaneous%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThose%20who%20opposed%20simultaneous%20elections%20raised%20apprehensions%20that%20its%20adoption%20could%20violate%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20be%20anti-democratic%20and%20anti-federal%2C%20marginalise%20regional%20parties%2C%20encourage%20the%20dominance%20of%20national%20parties%20and%20result%20in%20a%20presidential%20form%20of%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20parties%20in%20favour%20included%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20National%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20the%20All%20Jharkhand%20Student%20Union%2C%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20(Soney%20Lal)%2C%20the%20Asom%20Gana%20Parishad%2C%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%2C%20the%20Lok%20Jan%20Shakti%20Party%20(R)%2C%20the%20Mizo%20National%20Front%2C%20the%20Nationalist%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Party%2C%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20the%20Sikkim%20Krantikari%20Morcha%2C%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20and%20the%20United%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20Liberal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20parties%20in%20favour%20included%20the%20Pattali%20Makkal%20Katchi%2C%20the%20Republican%20Party%20of%20India%20(Athawale)%2C%20the%20Tamil%20Maanila%20Congress%20(M)%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20the%20United%20Kisan%20Vikas%20Party%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Samaj%20Party%2C%20the%20Gorkha%20National%20Liberal%20Front%2C%20the%20Hindustani%20Awam%20Morcha%2C%20the%20Indian%20Makkal%20Kalvi%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20the%20Indigenous%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%20of%20Tripura%2C%20the%20Jan%20Surajay%20Shakti%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Jan%20Shakti%20Party%2C%20the%20Maharashtrawadi%20Gomantak%20Party%2C%20the%20Nishad%20Party%2C%20the%20Puthia%20Nidhi%20Katchi%2C%20the%20Rashtrawadi%20Congress%20Party%20(Ajit%20Pawar)%20and%20the%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Azad%20Party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20parties%20who%20opposed%20simultaneous%20elections%20included%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%2C%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20the%20All%20India%20United%20Democratic%20Front%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Majilis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20the%20Naga%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%2C%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20the%20Marumalarchi%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20the%20Viduthalai%20Chiruthaigal%20Katchi%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist-Leninist)%20Liberation%20and%20the%20Social%20Democratic%20Party%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlanning%20for%20simultaneous%20polls%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20recommended%20that%20in%20order%20to%20prepare%20for%20logistical%20arrangements%20for%20simultaneous%20polls%2C%20the%20ECI%20(in%20the%20case%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assembly%20elections)%20and%20the%20state%20election%20commissions%20(in%20the%20case%20of%20municipal%20and%20panchayat%20elections)%C2%A0should%20make%20a%20plan%20for%20the%20advance%20procurement%20of%20equipment%20including%20EVMs%20and%20VVPATs%20as%20well%20as%20the%20deployment%20of%20security%20forces%20and%20polling%20personnel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Coverwhelming%20support%E2%80%9D%20for%20simultaneous%20elections%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20spur%20%5Bthe%5D%20development%20process%20and%20social%20cohesion%2C%20deepen%20the%20foundations%20of%20our%20democratic%20rubric%20and%20realise%20the%20aspirations%20of%20India%2C%20that%20is%20Bharat%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710436857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26110403%2FThe-Wire-56.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsimultaneous-polls-kovind-panel-lays-down-synchronisation-of-terms-cutting-short-assembly-tenures%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20panel's%2018%2C626-page%20report%20stated%20that%20it%20had%20received%20responses%20from%2047%20political%20parties%2C%2015%20of%20which%20opposed%20simultaneous%20polls.%20These%20parties%20cited%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20potential%20violation%20of%20the%20constitution's%20basic%20structure%2C%20anti-federalism%2C%20and%20the%20marginalisation%20of%20regional%20parties.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%2