13094644%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbelgium-football-association-unveils-new-tintin-inspired-kit-for-summer-european-championship-13094644%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Startup%20movement%20must%20be%20driven%20by%20domestic%20financing%2C%20says%20Amitabh%20Kant%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710430262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-03%2F31%2Ffull%2F1680244280-754.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fstartup-movement-must-be-driven-by-domestic-financing-says-amitabh-kant-124031400973_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20speaking%20at%20the%20CII%20Unicorn%20Summit%2C%20Kant%20said%20the%20nation%20needs%20to%20create%20a%20fund%20of%20funds%20to%20support%20young%20deep%20tech%20startups%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fstartup-movement-must-be-driven-by-domestic-financing-says-amitabh-kant-124031400973_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fstartup-movement-must-be-driven-by-domestic-financing-says-amitabh-kant-124031400973_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Fstartup-movement-must-be-driven-by-domestic-financing-says-amitabh-kant-124031400973_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Energy%20Subsidies%20High%3B%20Fossil%20Fuel%20Subsidies%20More%20Than%20Renewables%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F14090239%2Fred-zeppelin-UVGE-o757-g-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20subsidised%20a%20whopping%20Rs%203.2%20lakh%20crore%20energy%20sources%2C%20including%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20renewable%20energy%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%202023%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20by%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20(IISD).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20released%20on%20March%2012%20mentioned%20that%20energy%20subsidies%20reflect%20a%20nine-year%20high%20for%20the%20country%2C%20and%20come%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20However%2C%20subsidies%20for%20renewable%20energy%20made%20up%20only%2010%25%20of%20this%20amount.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShifting%20support%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20clean%20energy%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20socially%20responsible%20manner%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20or%20ensuring%20a%20just%20transition%20%E2%80%93%20will%20be%20important%20for%20India%20to%20achieve%20its%20global%20commitments%20such%20as%20achieving%2050%25%20cumulative%20electric%20power%20installed%20capacity%20from%20non-fossil%20sources%20by%202030%2C%20energy%20independence%20by%202047%2C%20and%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%202070%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFossil%20fuel%20subsidies%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iisd.org%2Fstory%2Fmapping-india-energy-policy-2023%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMapping%20India%E2%80%99s%20Energy%20Policy%3A%20A%20Decade%20in%20Action%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20shows%20that%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20show%20an%20interesting%20pattern.%20In%20what%20could%20be%20a%20good%20sign%2C%20it%20has%20declined%20by%2059%25%20since%202014%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Can%20accomplishment%20that%20many%20other%20large%20economies%20have%20struggled%20to%20achieve%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20the%20report.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20finer%20details%20tell%20a%20slightly%20different%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202022%20energy%20crisis%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20and%20the%20increasing%20demand%20for%20power%20in%20India%20have%20caused%20the%20country%20to%20encourage%20%E2%80%9Call%20forms%20of%20energy%20supplies%20and%20adopt%20a%20mixed%20approach%20to%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20clean%20energy%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20figures%20from%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20also%20show%20that%20coal%20accounts%20for%2045%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20primary%20energy%20supply%20in%202022%2C%20up%20from%2043%25%20in%202020.%20Altogether%2C%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20were%20five%20times%20greater%20than%20clean%20energy%20subsidies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20fiscal%20year%202023%20alone%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20subsidies%20rose%20at%20least%20Rs%2070%2C692%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20a%20staggering%2063%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year.%20Coal%20subsidies%20reached%20almost%20Rs%2050%2C000%20crore%20in%20FY%202023%3A%20but%20this%20is%20only%20a%2017%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20FY%202022.%20The%20central%20government%20provided%20at%20least%20ten%20different%20subsidies%20to%20coal%2C%20but%20the%20largest%20in%202023%20were%20tax%20expenditures%20(concessional%20custom%20duty%20on%20imported%20coal%20and%20a%20concessional%20GST%20rate).%20To%20meet%20its%20rising%20energy%20demands%2C%20India%20also%20relied%20a%20lot%20on%20coal%20imports%20in%202023.%20Non-coking%20coal%20imports%20rose%20by%2020%25%20by%20volume%20that%20year.%20As%20per%20the%20report%2C%20this%20is%20the%20highest%20growth%20in%20non-coking%20coal%20imports%20since%202015.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20consumer%20price%20support%20for%20electricity%20still%20continues%20to%20grow%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%20It%20was%20the%20single%20largest%20subsidy%20mechanism%20in%202023%2C%20accounting%20for%2050%25%20of%20all%20energy%20subsidies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20have%20reduced%20by%2059%25%20since%20their%20peak%20in%202013-14%2C%20without%20further%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etargeting%20and%20a%20return%20to%20a%20market-based%20pricing%20regime%2C%20they%20could%20mount%20again%2C%20resulting%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebudgetary%20impacts%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20co-author%20of%20the%20report%20Swasti%20Raizada%2C%20policy%20advisor%20at%20IISD.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20undesirable%20as%20untargeted%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20are%20an%20inefficient%20way%20of%20supporting%20low-income%20households%2C%20and%20they%20shrink%20the%20fiscal%20space%20available%20for%20supporting%20clean%20energy%20technologies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raizada%20added%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERenewable%20energy%20and%20EVs%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202023%2C%20both%20clean%20energy%20and%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20grew%20by%20around%2040%25%20with%20subsidies%20for%20renewable%20energy%20and%20electric%20vehicles%20growing%20slightly%20faster.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20renewable%20energy%20subsidies%20increased%20to%20Rs%2014%2C843%20crore%2C%20an%208%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20FY%202022.%20These%20subsidies%2C%20however%2C%20still%20remain%20fairly%20low%20when%20compared%20to%20that%20afforded%20to%20fossil%20fuels%20during%20this%20time.%20The%20clean%20energy%20subsidies%20accounted%20for%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20total%20energy%20subsidies%2C%20while%20subsidies%20for%20coal%2C%20oil%2C%20and%20gas%20contributed%20around%2040%25.%20The%20majority%20of%20the%20remaining%20subsidies%20were%20for%20electricity%20consumption%2C%20particularly%20in%20agriculture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COngoing%20high%20levels%20of%20public%20financial%20support%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20not%20only%20undermine%20emission%20reduction%20goals%20but%20also%20perpetuate%20dependence%20on%20price-volatile%20and%20geopolitically%20risky%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20which%20weakens%20energy%20security%20and%20affordability%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Finvestment-of-2-trillion-per-year-needed-to-meet-global-2030-renewable-energy-target%5C%22%3EInvestment%20of%20%242%20Trillion%20Per%20Year%20Needed%20to%20Meet%20Global%202030%20Renewable%20Energy%20Target%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20the%20think%20tank%20added%20in%20the%20report%3A%20%E2%80%9CShifting%20support%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20clean%20energy%20in%20a%20socially%20responsible%20manner%20provides%20a%20long-term%20solution%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20energy%20objectives%20and%20is%20consistent%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20achieving%2050%25%20cumulative%20electric%20power%20installed%20capacity%20from%20non-fossil%20sources%20by%202030%2C%20energy%20independence%20by%202047%2C%20and%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%202070.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20field%20in%20which%20India%20needs%20to%20improve%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report%2C%20is%20in%20subsidies%20being%20offered%20for%20electric%20vehicles%20(EVs).%20While%20subsidies%20for%20EVs%20reached%20an%20all-time%20high%20in%202023%20at%20Rs%209%2C798%20crore%2C%20and%20India%20emerged%20as%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20markets%20for%20EVs%2C%20the%20report%20recommends%20that%20EVs%20be%20%E2%80%9Cwider%20government%20support%E2%80%9D%20for%20%E2%80%9Cbusiness%20continuity%20and%20promoting%20further%20investments%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20it%C2%A0%20comes%20to%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20also%20needs%20to%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20cost-benefit%20analysis%20to%20allocate%20a%20portion%20of%20its%20energy%20revenues%20to%20meet%20its%20just%20transition%20needs%2C%20where%20the%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20are%20replaced%20with%20renewable%20and%20clean%20energy%20options%20while%20also%20helping%20communities%20dependent%20on%20fossil%20fuel-based%20livelihood%20measures%20transition%20gradually.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHigher%20taxes%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20will%20also%20help%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20revenues%20that%20come%20from%20this%20can%20be%20used%20to%20support%20economically%20backward%20communities%2C%20the%20report%20mentioned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPrevious%20studies%20show%20that%20India%20will%20require%20significant%20investment%20to%20make%20its%20energy%20transition%20just%2C%20sustainable%2C%20and%20inclusive%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Deepak%20Sharma%2C%20policy%20analyst%20at%20IISD%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20state-owned%20enterprises%20will%20be%20a%20critical%20part%20of%20this%20shift.%20As%20their%20majority%20shareholder%2C%20the%20government%20should%20ensure%20that%20all%20fresh%20capital%20going%20to%20these%20entities%20is%20linked%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20net%20zero%20commitments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710430233000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F14090239%2Fred-zeppelin-UVGE-o757-g-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Findias-energy-subsidies-high-fossil-fuel-subsidies-more-than-renewables%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shifting%20support%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20clean%20energy%20while%20also%20ensuring%20a%20just%20transition%20will%20be%20important%20for%20India%20to%20achieve%20i