%22%3A%22The%20trust%20is%20an%20infrastructure%20investment%20trust%20(InvIT)%2C%20a%20special%20investment%20vehicle%20in%20which%20IRB%20Infra%20holds%20a%2051%20per%20cent%20stake%20and%2049%20per%20cent%20equity%20is%20held%20by%20affiliates%20of%20GIC%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fferrovial-arm-cintra-to-acquire-24-stake-in-irb-infra-invit-from-gic-124031400971_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fferrovial-arm-cintra-to-acquire-24-stake-in-irb-infra-invit-from-gic-124031400971_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fferrovial-arm-cintra-to-acquire-24-stake-in-irb-infra-invit-from-gic-124031400971_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commission%20Uploads%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Data%2C%20No%20Info%20on%20Who%20Paid%20Whom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20day%20before%20its%20court-ordered%20deadline%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20has%20uploaded%20data%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20and%20encashed%20since%202019%20onto%20its%20website%2C%20it%20said%20in%20a%20press%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20provided%20it%20the%20data%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20press%20note%2C%20the%20ECI%20said%20it%20uploaded%20the%20data%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20and%20%E2%80%9Cas%20received%20from%20%5Bthe%5D%20SBI%20on%20%5Ban%5D%20%E2%80%98as%20is%20where%20is%E2%80%99%20basis%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20had%20made%20this%20data%20available%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fcandidate-politicalparty%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fcandidate-politicalparty%3C%2Fa%3E%20URL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20may%20be%20recalled%20that%20in%20the%20said%20matter%2C%20ECI%20has%20consistently%20and%20categorically%20weighed%20in%20favour%20of%20disclosure%20and%20transparency%2C%20a%20position%20reflected%20in%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20noted%20in%20the%20order%20also%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ECI%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20are%20interest-free%20financial%20instruments%20that%20individuals%20or%20groups%20may%20buy%20to%20make%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Ein%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20the%20bonds%20violated%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information%20and%20were%20thus%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20asked%20the%20SBI%20to%20provide%20data%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20and%20encashed%20since%20April%2012%2C%202019%20to%20the%20ECI%20by%20March%206%2C%20although%20the%20bank%20did%20so%20only%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20the%20court%20rejected%20its%20request%20for%20extra%20time%20till%20the%20end%20of%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fdisclosure-of-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Euploaded%20two%20sets%20of%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20file%20contains%20the%20details%20of%20companies%20that%20bought%20the%20bonds%20and%20the%20other%20file%20contains%20a%20list%20of%20political%20parties%20that%20encashed%20the%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20data%20published%20by%20the%20ECI%20on%20Thursday%20gives%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20the%20corporations%20and%20private%20business%20houses%20that%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20between%202019%20and%202024%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20provide%20any%20information%20on%20which%20party%20redeemed%20the%20bonds%20of%20what%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20be%20in%20contravention%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20that%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme.%20The%20court%20clearly%20observed%20that%20the%20opacity%20surrounding%20the%20political%20donations%20could%20be%20the%20basis%20of%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20between%20companies%20and%20political%20parties%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20electoral%20bonds%20contained%20a%20unique%20identification%20number%20%E2%80%93%20or%20what%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunique%20matching%20code%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20could%20be%20used%20to%20match%20each%20donor%20to%20the%20beneficiary%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%2C%20the%20SBI%20could%20have%20easily%20furnished%20details%20about%20which%20political%20party%20redeemed%20which%20bonds%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20top%20court%20had%20ended%20the%20controversial%20scheme%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20the%20data%20uploaded%20makes%20it%20rather%20difficult%20to%20infer%20whether%20there%20were%20any%20quid%20pro%20quo%20dealings%20between%20companies%20which%20bought%20the%20bonds%20and%20different%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20whether%20the%20SBI%20will%20furnish%20these%20details%20soon%20or%20if%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%C2%A0matter%C2%A0again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20have%20also%20questioned%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20motivations%20given%20that%20it%20promptly%20handed%20over%20the%20data%20on%20Tuesday%20despite%20it%20asking%20for%20three%20months%E2%80%99%20extra%20time%20just%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20files%20shared%20by%20the%20SBI%20expose%20a%20close%20nexus%20between%20corporations%20and%20political%20parties%2C%20especially%20the%20ruling%20BJP%2C%20which%20has%20received%20the%20maximum%20donations%20of%20any%20party%20from%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nexus%20was%20well-known%20but%20is%20now%20backed%20by%20solid%20data%2C%20even%20though%20the%20SBI%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20bank%2C%20has%20attempted%20to%20retain%20a%20layer%20of%20darkness%20around%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EECI%20seeks%20modification%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20order%2C%20says%20advocate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20posted%20on%20social%20media%20that%20the%20ECI%20has%20also%20filed%20%E2%80%9Can%20application%20to%20modify%20the%20SC%20%5BSupreme%20Court%5D%20order%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%E2%80%9D%20and%20alleged%20that%20after%20the%20SBI%20tried%20to%20hide%20information%20by%20moving%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20ECI%20was%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accused%20the%20SBI%20and%20ECI%20of%20acting%20like%20%E2%80%9Ccaged%20parrots%E2%80%9D%20to%20protect%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20which%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdesperate%20to%20hide%20information%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20analysis%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20revealed%20that%20the%20BJP%20received%20nearly%20Rs%206%2C565%20crore%20or%2055%25%20of%20the%20total%20funds%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20between%20March%202018%20and%20January%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20national%20rival%2C%20the%20Congress%2C%20garnered%20a%20mere%209.3%25%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2016%2C518.11%20crore%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20through%20the%20bonds%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remaining%20amount%20was%20shared%20by%20other%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20February%20order%2C%20the%20SBI%20was%20asked%20to%20include%20in%20its%20disclosure%20the%20date%20bonds%20were%20purchased%20on%2C%20their%20denominations%20and%20the%20names%20of%20those%20who%20purchased%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20ordered%20for%20data%20on%20every%20electoral%20bond%20encashed%20by%20political%20parties%20since%20April%2012%2C%202019%20to%20be%20furnished%2C%20including%20the%20date%20they%20were%20encashed%20on%20and%20the%20bonds%E2%80%99%20denominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20before%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20original%20deadline%2C%20the%20SBI%20said%20it%20would%20need%20time%20till%20June%2030%20this%20year%20because%20it%20had%20to%20compile%2044%2C434%20sets%20of%20information%20from%20two%20%E2%80%98silos%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20court%20asked%20the%20bank%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20data%20by%20March%206%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20may%20proceed%20against%20the%20bank%20on%20grounds%20on%20wilful%20disobedience%20if%20it%20did%20not%20meet%20this%20new%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20a%20developing%20story.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710427817000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-uploads-electoral-bonds-data%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20nature%20of%20the%20data%20uploaded%20to%20the%20ECI's%20website%20makes%20it%20rather%20difficult%20to%20infer%20whether%20there%20were%20any%20quid%20pro%20quo%20dealings%20between%20companies%20which%20bought%20the%20bonds%20and%20different%20governments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-uploads-electoral-bonds-data%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2267%25%20of%20Indian%20healthcare%20companies%20form%20ESG%20boards%3A%2