20almost%20double%20that%20of%20the%20world's%20second%20most%20powerful%20rocket%2C%20NASA's%20Space%20Launch%20System%20(SLS)%20--%20though%20the%20latter%20is%20now%20certified%2C%20while%20Starship%20is%20still%20a%20prototype.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarship's%20third%20launch%20test%20in%20its%20fully%20stacked%20configuration%20is%20set%20to%20be%20its%20most%20ambitious%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObjectives%20include%20opening%20and%20closing%20Starship's%20payload%20door%20to%20test%20its%20ability%20to%20deliver%20satellites%20and%20other%20cargo%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20also%20aims%20to%20re-light%20the%20ship's%20engines%20in%20space%2C%20and%20perform%20an%20onboard%20test%20that%20will%20help%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20future%20Starships%20to%20refuel%20one%20another%20in%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarship's%20planned%20trajectory%20sees%20it%20fly%20halfway%20around%20the%20globe%2C%20brake%20in%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20then%20freefall%20to%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20just%20over%20an%20hour%20after%20launch%2C%20and%20probably%20break%20up%20and%20explode%20on%20impact.%20Soft%20splashdowns%20are%20planned%20for%20future%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20has%20been%20developing%20prototypes%20of%20Starship%20since%202018%2C%20and%20early%20tests%20involved%20short%20hops%20of%20just%20the%20upper%20stage%2C%20which%20is%20also%20referred%20to%20as%20Starship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Third%20time%20lucky%3F%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bintegrated%26quot%3B%20test%20came%20in%20April%202023.%20SpaceX%20was%20forced%20to%20blow%20up%20Starship%20within%20a%20few%20minutes%20of%20launch%2C%20because%20the%20two%20stages%20failed%20to%20separate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rocket%20disintegrated%20into%20a%20ball%20of%20fire%20and%20crashed%20into%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%2C%20sending%20a%20dust%20cloud%20over%20a%20town%20several%20miles%20(kilometers)%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20test%20in%20November%202023%20fared%20slightly%20better%3A%20The%20booster%20separated%20from%20the%20spaceship%2C%20but%20both%20then%20exploded%20over%20the%20ocean%2C%20in%20what%20the%20company%20euphemistically%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Brapid%20unscheduled%20disassembly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20closed%20a%20probe%20into%20the%20incident%20last%20month%20after%20identifying%2017%20corrective%20actions%20SpaceX%20needed%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20%26quot%3Brapid%20iterative%20development%26quot%3B%20strategy%20has%20paid%20off%20for%20the%20company%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20Falcon%209%20rockets%20have%20come%20to%20be%20workhorses%20for%20NASA%20and%20the%20commercial%20sector%2C%20its%20Dragon%20capsule%20sends%20astronauts%20and%20cargo%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20and%20its%20Starlink%20internet%20satellite%20constellation%20now%20covers%20dozens%20of%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20clock%20is%20ticking%20down%20for%20SpaceX%20to%20be%20ready%20for%20NASA's%20planned%20return%20of%20astronauts%20to%20the%20Moon%20in%202026%2C%20using%20a%20modified%20Starship%20as%20the%20lander%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20SpaceX%20need%20to%20prove%20it%20can%20launch%2C%20fly%20and%20land%20Starship%20safely%20--%20it%20must%20eventually%20also%20show%20it%20can%20send%20multiple%20%26quot%3BStarship%20tankers%26quot%3B%20into%20orbit%20to%20refuel%20a%20main%20Starship%20for%20its%20onward%20journey%20to%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710424860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Facjbpe9g_starship-3rd-test-flight-_625x300_14_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspacexs-starsh