%20of%20Police%20D%20Ramesh.%20Mr%20Ramesh%20had%20said%20he%20filed%20the%20complaint%20after%20he%20found%20many%20physical%20and%20electronic%20documents%20had%20gone%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20had%20told%20NDTV%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20Rao%20had%20allegedly%20also%20illegally%20tapped%20the%20phones%20of%20nearly%2050%20key%20people%2C%20including%20opposition%20members%2C%20in%20the%20state%2C%20which%20was%20then%20ruled%20by%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS).%20Phones%20of%20family%20members%20of%20some%20people%20close%20to%20the%20BRS%20had%20also%20allegedly%20been%20snooped%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SIB%20is%20supposed%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20left-wing%20extremism%2C%20but%20a%20team%20headed%20by%20Rao%20was%20reportedly%20gathering%20political%20intelligence%20and%20details%20of%20transactions%20made%20by%20opposition%20party%20leaders%2C%20the%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20senior%20officer%20is%20accused%20of%20not%20only%20erasing%2010%20lakh%20call%20records%20a%20day%20after%20the%20elections%20but%20also%20turning%20off%20CCTV%20cameras%20and%20replacing%20the%20hard%20drives%20he%20had%20destroyed%20with%20new%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20first%20information%20report%20based%20on%20Mr%20Ramesh's%20complaint%2C%20Rao%20had%20two%20rooms%20to%20himself%20in%20the%20SIB%20and%20operated%20with%2017%20systems.%20He%20also%20had%20an%20exclusive%20and%20dedicated%20leased%20line%20with%20an%20internet%20connection.%20Through%20this%20setup%2C%20he%20%26quot%3Bdeveloped%20profiles%20of%20unknown%20persons%20and%20monitored%20the%20same%20clandestinely%2C%20unauthorisedly%20and%20illegally%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20FIR%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Rao%20was%20sent%20to%20judicial%20custody%20for%2014%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710424080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fuct7btb8_praneeth-rao-telangana-_625x300_14_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farrested-telangana-cop-said-he-destroyed-intel-on-his-boss-orders-sources-5238374%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20case%20involving%20arrested%20former%20senior%20police%20officer%20Praneeth%20Rao%20has%20become%20murkier%20with%20the%20cop%20alleging%20that%20he%20had%20destroyed%2050%20hard%20drives%20containing%20lakhs%20of%20intelligence%20documents%20on%20the%20orders%20of%20his%20former%20boss%2C%20sources%20have%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farrested-telangana-cop-said-he-destroyed-intel-on-his-boss-orders-sources-5238374%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farrested-telangana-cop-said-he-destroyed-intel-on-his-boss-orders-sources-5238374%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farrested-telangana-cop-said-he-destroyed-intel-on-his-boss-orders-sources-5238374%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Human%20Development%20Index%3A%20India%20Ranks%20134th%2C%20Falls%20Behind%20Bangladesh%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Bhutan%20and%20China%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15173435%2FMumbai.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20ranks%20at%20134%20on%20the%20global%20Human%20Development%20Index%20(HDI)%2C%20according%20to%20United%20Nations%20Development%20Programme%E2%80%99s%20(UNDP%E2%80%99s)%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhdr.undp.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fglobal-report-document%2Fhdr2023-24reporten.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20human%20development.%20The%20report%20also%20revealed%20that%20affluent%20countries%20are%20experiencing%20unprecedented%20levels%20of%20growth%2C%20while%20half%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20poorest%20nations%20have%20failed%20to%20regain%20their%20pre-pandemic%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%202023%2F24%20Human%20Development%20Report%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Breaking%20the%20Gridlock%3A%20Reimagining%20cooperation%20in%20a%20polarized%20world%2C%E2%80%99%20while%20HDI%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%20record%20highs%20in%202023%20after%20declines%20in%202020%20and%202021%2C%20there%20is%20a%20stark%20contrast%20in%20development%20levels%20between%20rich%20and%20poor%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20points%20out%20that%20global%20inequalities%20have%20been%20compounded%20by%20substantial%20economic%20concentration%20%E2%80%93%20almost%2040%25%20of%20global%20trade%20in%20goods%20is%20concentrated%20in%20three%20or%20fewer%20countries.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20market%20capitalisation%20of%20each%20of%20the%20three%20largest%20tech%20companies%20in%20the%20world%20surpassed%20the%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%20(GDP)%20of%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20countries%20that%20year%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20widening%20human%20development%20gap%20revealed%20by%20the%20report%20shows%20that%20the%20two-decade%20trend%20of%20steadily%20reducing%20inequalities%20between%20wealthy%20and%20poor%20nations%20is%20now%20in%20reverse.%20Despite%20our%20deeply%20interconnected%20global%20societies%2C%20we%20are%20falling%20short.%20We%20must%20leverage%20our%20interdependence%20as%20well%20as%20our%20capacities%20to%20address%20our%20shared%20and%20existential%20challenges%20and%20ensure%20people%E2%80%99s%20aspirations%20are%20met%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Achim%20Steiner%2C%20head%20of%20the%20UN%20Development%20Programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20gridlock%20carries%20a%20significant%20human%20toll.%20The%20failure%20of%20collective%20action%20to%20advance%20action%20on%20climate%20change%2C%20digitalisation%20or%20poverty%20and%20inequality%20not%20only%20hinders%20human%20development%20but%20also%20worsens%20polarisation%20and%20further%20erodes%20trust%20in%20people%20and%20institutions%20worldwide%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20rank%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECategorised%20as%20%E2%80%98Very%20High%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98High%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Medium%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Low%20Human%20Development%E2%80%99%2C%20China%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20ranked%20at%2075%20and%2078%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20the%20High%20Human%20Development%20category%20compared%20to%20India%2C%20which%20stands%20at%20134.%20India%20also%20ranks%20below%20Bhutan%20(125)%20and%20Bangladesh%20(129)%2C%20despite%20all%20three%20being%20categorised%20under%20%E2%80%98Medium%20Human%20Development%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Democracy%20paradox%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20while%20nine%20in%2010%20people%20worldwide%20endorse%20democracy%2C%20over%20half%20of%20the%20respondents%20expressed%20support%20for%20leaders%20that%20may%20undermine%20it%20by%20bypassing%20fundamental%20rules%20of%20the%20democratic%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%20paradox%2C%20half%20of%20the%20people%20surveyed%20reported%20having%20no%20or%20limited%20control%20over%20their%20lives%2C%20and%20over%20two-thirds%20believed%20that%20they%20have%20little%20influence%20on%20their%20government%E2%80%99s%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20polarisation%20in%20countries%20is%20also%20responsible%20for%20protectionist%20or%20%3Cspan%3Einward-turning%20policy%20approaches%20which%20is%20%E2%80%9Cstarkly%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20global%20cooperation%20needed%20to%20address%20urgent%20issues%20like%20the%20decarbonisation%20of%20our%20economies%2C%20misuse%20of%20digital%20technologies%2C%20and%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20says%20while%20emphasising%20on%20the%20need%20for%20united%20action%20to%20tackle%20global%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20world%20marked%20by%20increasing%20polarisation%20and%20division%2C%20neglecting%20to%20invest%20in%20each%20other%20poses%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20our%20wellbeing%20and%20security.%20Protectionist%20approaches%20cannot%20address%20the%20complex%2C%20interconnected%20challenges%20we%20face%2C%20including%20pandemic%20prevention%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20digital%20regulation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Steiner%20added.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20problems%20are%20intertwined%2C%20requiring%20equally%20interconnected%20solutions.%20By%20adopting%20an%20opportunity-driven%20agenda%20that%20emphasises%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20energy%20transition%20and%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20for%20human%20development%2C%20we%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20break%20through%20the%20current%20deadlock%20and%20reignite%20a%20commitment%20to%20a%20shared%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710423907000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15173435%2FMumbai.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhuman-development-index-india-ranks-134th-falls-behind-bangladesh-sri-lanka-bhutan-and-china%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20revealed%20that%20affluent%20countries%20are%20experiencing%20unprecedented%20levels%20of%20growth%2C%20while%20half%20of%20the%20world's%20poorest%20nations%20have%20failed%20to%20regain%20their%20pre-pandemic%20progress.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhuman-development-index-india-ranks-134th-falls-behind-bangladesh-sri-lanka-bhutan-and-china%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20%E2%80%98Mera%20Pehla%20Vote%20%E2%80%93%20Desh%20Ke%20Liye%E2%80%99%20Campaign%2C%20Election%20Commission%20Openly%20Boosts%20for%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14160955%2Fimage-1954.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%20is%20rapidly%20digitising.%20There%20are%20good%20things%20and%20bad%2C%20speed-bumps%20on%20the%20way%20and%20caveats%20to%20be%20mindful%20of.%20The%20weekly%20column%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3ETerminal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0focuses%20on%20all%20that%20is%20connected%20and%20is%20not%20%E2%80%93%20on%20digital%20issues%2C%20policy%2C%20ideas%20and%20themes%20dominating%20the%20conversation%20in%20India%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20has%20been%20clearly%20abdicating%20its%20responsibilities%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20as%20control%20over%20its%20functions%20are%20being%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20state.%20The%20latest%20in%20the%20row%20is%20the%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20for%20first%20time%20voters%20with%20%3Cem%3EMera%20Pehla%20Vote%20%E2%80%93%20Desh%20Ke%20Liye%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%20launched%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20being%20promoted%20by%20various%20departments%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20takes%20over%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20functions.%C2%A0%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpledge.mygov.in%2Fmera-pehla-vote%2F%5C%22%3EMyGov%20pledge%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecampaign%20for%20the%20same%20forces%20voters%20to%20share%20their%20personal%20information%20with%20an%20OTP%20verification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20responsibility%20of%20registering%20voters%2C%20educating%20voters%20and%20encouraging%20voters%20participating%20in%20elections%20is%20clearly%20the%20constitutional%20mandate%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%20Yet%2C%20we%20now%20see%20a%20takeover%20of%20this%20function%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20with%20activities%20of%20taking%20pledges%20from%20first%20time%20voters%20in%20the%20name%20of%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%