ands%20of%20political%20parties%2C%20which%20use%20it%20for%20electioneering%20purposes.%20Personal%20data%20collected%20by%20political%20parties%20then%20influences%20government%20policy%20after%20elections%2C%20and%20information%20gathered%20by%20parties%20in%20power%20during%20their%20governance%20is%20used%20in%20future%20elections.%20This%20forms%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20personal%20data%20in%20electoral%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20ECI%20is%20aware%20of%20this%20issue%2C%20it%20has%20not%20taken%20proactive%20measures%20to%20address%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20the%20ECI%20being%20silent%20about%20the%20misuse%20of%20state%20resources%20as%20part%20of%20this%20campaign%2C%20it%20is%20promoting%20it.%20Along%20with%20several%20departments%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20the%20ECI%20and%20its%20chief%20electoral%20officers%20are%20promoting%20this%20campaign%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EOur%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FDemocracy%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20banking%20on%20you%20%E2%80%93%20we%20appeal%20to%20all%20Voters%20to%20exercise%20their%20franchise!%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FElections2024%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Elections2024%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FChunavKaParv%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23ChunavKaParv%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FDeskKaGarv%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23DeskKaGarv%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FECI%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23ECI%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FSVEEP%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23SVEEP%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FMeraPehlaVoteDeshKeliye%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23MeraPehlaVoteDeshKeliye%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FncbobZgOtf%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FncbobZgOtf%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(%40ECISVEEP)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FECISVEEP%2Fstatus%2F1766711426083958913%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2010%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20abuse%20of%20state%20machinery%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20but%20is%20seen%20across%20various%20state%20governments.%20In%20case%20of%20political%20campaigns%2C%20it%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20ECI%20to%20monitor%20them%20and%20safeguard%20the%20rights%20of%20voters.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20personal%20data%20in%20elections%2C%20ECI%20has%20always%20ignored%20its%20responsibility%20to%20uphold%20fairness%20in%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20five%20years%20of%20Cambridge%20Analytica%2C%20the%20ECI%20has%20consistently%20ignored%20the%20question%20of%20personal%20data%20and%20micro-targeting%20of%20voters.%20As%20India%20goes%20for%20another%20General%20Election%2C%20ECI%20is%20not%20only%20silent%20about%20these%20issues%2C%20it%20is%20openly%20supporting%20the%20abuse%20of%20electoral%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%2C%20by%20Parliament%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20lack%20of%20enforcement%20of%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Act%20has%20specific%20provisions%20to%20ensure%20data%20is%20not%20used%20in%20elections%2C%20it%20is%20not%20being%20enforced.%20With%20no%20rules%20in%20sight%2C%20the%20ECI%20is%20also%20going%20to%20ignore%20the%20role%20of%20personal%20data%20in%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ECI%20has%20also%20ignored%20the%20regulation%20of%20the%20social%20media%20and%20online%20advertising%20industry%20by%20allowing%20them%20to%20self-regulate.%20While%20it%20actively%20regulates%20print%20and%20broadcast%20media%20through%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%2C%20the%20same%20rules%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20apply%20to%20the%20world%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20completely%20obfuscated%20its%20communications%20to%20social%20media%20companies%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%20categorising%20them%20as%20third-party%20information%20that%20the%20commission%20cannot%20even%20share%20with%20the%20public.%20Any%20censorship%20of%20social%20media%20content%20ordered%20by%20the%20ECI%20is%20again%20closed%20with%20no%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20been%20increased%20activity%20related%20to%20the%20role%20of%20AI%20and%20DeepFakes%20in%20elections%2C%20the%20ECI%20has%20largely%20neglected%20to%20establish%20any%20rules%20or%20guidelines%20regarding%20this%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20flurry%20of%20notices%20and%20advisories%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20related%20to%20AI%20and%20what%20content%20they%20might%20produce%2C%20ECI%20is%20unlikely%20to%20act%20on%20this%20issue%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Fintl%2Fen-in%2Fcompany-news%2Foutreach-initiatives%2Fsupporting-the-2024-indian-general-election%2F%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%20by%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20describes%20its%20support%20to%20the%20ECI%20in%20promoting%20election-related%20and%20self-regulation%20activities%20for%20the%20upcoming%20General%20Elections.%20Yet%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20general%20norms%20across%20the%20industry%20should%20ideally%20be%20a%20concern%20for%20the%20ECI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unlikely%20there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20any%20solutions%20to%20the%20electoral%20challenges%20being%20encountered%20in%20our%20digital%20society.%20But%20the%20lack%20of%20intent%20to%20even%20attempt%20to%20address%20these%20problems%20from%20the%20ECI%20shows%20it%20has%20completely%20abdicated%20its%20responsibility%20to%20host%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fskodali%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ESrinivas%20Kodali%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20is%20a%20researcher%20on%20digitisation%20and%20a%20hacktivist.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710423034000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14160955%2Fimage-1954.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwith-mera-pehla-vote-desh-ke-liye-campaign-election-commission-openly-boosts-for-govt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20election%20campaign%20being%20%E2%80%9Claunched%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%9D%20raises%20doubts%20and%20eyebrows.%20Does%20getting%20in%20a%20contestant%20for%20the%20polls%20for%20what%20is%20an%20EC%20activity%2C%20uphold%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98level%20playing%20field%E2%80%99%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwith-mera-pehla-vote-desh-ke-liye-campaign-election-commission-openly-boosts-for-govt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shaan%20on%20his%20connection%20with%20Kishore%20Da%20-%20Excl%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710423000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fthumb%2Fmsid-108494592%2Cwidth-1070%2Cheight-580%2Cimgsize-9562%2Cresizemode-75%2Coverlay-toi_sw%2Cpt-32%2Cy_pad-40%2Fphoto.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fshaan-very-early-in-life-i-realized-that-i-would-never-be-able-to-sound-like-kishore-kumar-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F108494518.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5