%2Famp_articleshow%2F108497052.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fsouth-korean-scientists-grow-beef-cells-in-rice-as-protein-alternative%2Famp_articleshow%2F108497052.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CAA%3A%20Top%20Lawyers%20Differ%3B%20Sibal%20Says%20%E2%80%98Totally%20Unconstitutional%E2%80%99%2C%20Dave%20Says%20%E2%80%98Doesn't%20Appear%20to%20Be%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14172656%2FKT-DD-KS.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Two%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20senior%20and%20most%20highly%20regarded%20lawyers%20have%20sharply%20differed%20over%20whether%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20of%202019%20(CAA)%20violates%20the%20constitution%20and%20also%20over%20whether%20the%20rules%20notified%20on%20Monday%20(March%2011)%20should%20be%20stayed%20till%20the%20200%20plus%20challenges%20to%20the%20Act%2C%20which%20have%20been%20admitted%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20are%20heard%20and%20decided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20divergence%20of%20opinion%20is%20marked%20and%20very%20clear%20and%20obvious.%20It%20illustrates%20two%20completely%20different%20attitudes%20and%20responses%20to%20both%20the%202019%20Act%20and%20the%20rules%20which%20were%20notified%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20in%20their%20personal%20opinion%20the%20CAA%20violates%20critical%20articles%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20a%20former%20law%20minister%2C%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CAbsolutely%2C%20without%20any%20doubt%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20this%20is%20because%20the%20Act%20bases%20citizenship%20on%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Dushyant%20Dave%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20answer%20is%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20give%E2%80%9D%20quickly%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20appear%20to%20be%20unconstitutional%20to%20me%E2%80%9D.%20He%20further%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20to%20say%20it%20is%20really%20unconstitutional%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20two%20separate%20interviews%2C%20presented%20together%20as%20a%20single%20package%2C%20both%20lawyers%20were%20asked%20almost%20identical%20questions.%20They%20were%20asked%20specifically%20whether%20the%20CAA%20violates%20Article%2014%2C%20which%20reads%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20shall%20not%20deny%20to%20any%20person%20equality%20before%20the%20law%20or%20the%20equal%20protection%20of%20the%20laws%20within%20the%20territory%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20said%20it%20did.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20certainly%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDave%20said%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20that%20was%20the%20case%20because%20as%20yet%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20not%20extended%20Article%2014%20to%20cover%20illegal%20immigrants.%20He%20said%20Article%2021%20covers%20everyone%20in%20the%20country%2C%20whether%20citizen%20or%20not.%20That%20is%20not%20the%20case%20with%20Article%2014%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20lawyers%20were%20also%20asked%20whether%20the%20CAA%20breaches%20the%20preambular%20commitment%20to%20secularism.%20Sibal%20said%20it%20does%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20present%20government%20has%20no%20commitment%20to%20secularism%20whatsoever.%20Dave%20said%20%E2%80%9Cit%20doesn%E2%80%99t%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%2C%20in%20his%20answer%20that%20the%20CAA%20may%20be%20illegal%20or%20morally%20questionable%20but%20not%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20over%20200%20challenges%20against%20the%20Act%2C%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20so%20far%20not%20responded%20to%20though%20almost%20five%20years%20have%20passed%2C%20Sibal%20said%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20should%20either%20stay%20the%20CAA%20rules%2C%20which%20were%20notified%20on%20Monday%2C%20or%20order%20no%20action%20is%20taken%20under%20them%20until%20it%20hears%20the%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20specific%20point%2C%20Dave%20repeatedly%20refused%20to%20comment%20and%20said%20it%20was%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20decide%20what%20it%20wishes%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20both%20lawyers%20believe%20that%20although%20the%20rules%20have%20been%20notified%20and%20in%20due%20course%20citizenship%20will%20start%20being%20conferred%20under%20the%20Act%2C%20the%20challenges%20have%20not%20become%20infructuous%20and%20the%20court%20can%20still%2C%20if%20it%20wants%2C%20strike%20down%20the%20Act%20whenever%20it%20hears%20the%20challenges.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it%20can%20turn%20the%20clock%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20is%20Sibal%20believes%20it%20should%20whilst%20Dave%20does%20not%20believe%20the%20Act%20is%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FQ2O2NZWkN_A%3Fsi%3Dp3ZK_k250H6cpFg0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20only%20given%20you%20the%20big%2C%20broad%20points.%20I%20have%20deliberately%20done%20so%20in%20apposition%20to%20and%20contrast%20with%20each%20other.%20There%E2%80%99s%20an%20awful%20lot%20more%20in%20the%20interviews%20which%20I%20will%20leave%20you%20to%20find%20out%20for%20yourself%20when%20you%20watch%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20will%20give%20you%20instead%20is%20a%20list%20of%20the%20questions.%20As%20I%20said%2C%20virtually%20the%20same%20questions%20were%20put%20to%20both%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20questions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20your%20personal%20opinion%2C%20does%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20the%20rules%20of%20which%20were%20notified%20on%20Monday%2C%20violate%20critical%20articles%20of%20the%20constitution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20constitution%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20shall%20not%20deny%20to%20any%20person%20equality%20before%20the%20law%20or%20the%20equal%20protection%20of%20the%20laws%20within%20the%20territory%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%20By%20excluding%20Muslims%2C%20does%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20breach%20Article%2014%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20preamble%20of%20the%20constitution%20declares%20India%20%E2%80%9Ca%20sovereign%20socialist%20secular%20democratic%20republic%E2%80%9D.%20Does%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20breach%20the%20commitment%20to%20secularism%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Act%20is%20designed%20to%20give%20citizenship%20to%20people%20who%20are%20discriminated%20on%20grounds%20of%20their%20religion%20in%20three%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20the%20choice%20of%20those%20three%20countries%20be%20questioned%20on%20constitutional%20grounds%3F%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Act%20ignores%20the%20Rohingyas%20from%20Myanmar%20and%20the%20Tamils%20from%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20are%20discriminated%20against%20and%20both%20countries%20are%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Even%20if%20you%20just%20focus%20on%20these%20three%20countries%2C%20the%20Act%20ignores%20Ahmadiyyas%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20Hazaras%2C%20who%20are%20Shias%2C%20from%20Afghanistan.%20They%20arguably%20face%20as%20much%20discrimination%20as%20Hindus%20and%20Christians%20in%20Pakistan%20or%20Hindus%20and%20Sikhs%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Now%2C%20challenges%20against%20this%20Act%20have%20been%20lying%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20since%202019.%20The%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20(March%2013)%20says%20there%20are%20over%20200%20such%20but%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20court.%20What%20message%20does%20that%20send%20out%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Now%20that%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20Act%20have%20been%20notified%20and%2C%20presumably%2C%20citizenship%20will%20soon%20be%20conferred%20under%20its%20terms%2C%20have%20those%20petitions%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20become%20infructuous%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20when%20questions%20were%20asked%20about%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delaying%20hearing%20the%20challenge%2C%20the%20court%20famously%20said%20we%20can%20turn%20the%20clock%20back%20if%20need%20be.%20Can%20the%20clock%20be%20turned%20back%20in%20this%20case%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710417754000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14172656%2FKT-DD-KS.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Ftop-lawyers-differ-on-caa-unconstitutional-kapil-sibal-not-so-dushyant-dave%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22However%2C%20both%20lawyers%20believe%20that%20although%20the%20rules%20have%20been%20notified%20and%20in%20due%20course%20citizenship%20will%20start%20being%20conferred%20under%20the%20Act%2C%20challenges%20to%20it%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20are%20not%20infructuous%20and%20that%20the%20clock%20can%20still%20be%20turned%20back.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Ftop-lawyers-differ-on-caa-unconstitutional-kapil-sibal-not-so-dushyant-dave%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wages%20Unchanged%20Since%202012%2C%20Almond%20Workers%20Earn%20Rs%202%2FKG%20in%20Delhi%20%7C%20Ground%20Report%20%7C%20Labour%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14154610%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-14-at-3.45.13-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20the%20past%2012%20days%2C%2