nked%20to%20the%20scandal%2C%20they%20were%20declared%20absconders%20for%20failing%20to%20appear%20in%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fex-pm-nawaz-sharifs-sons-arrest-warrants-in-panama-papers-scandal-linked-cases-cancelled%2Farticleshow%2F108494832.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fex-pm-nawaz-sharifs-sons-arrest-warrants-in-panama-papers-scandal-linked-cases-cancelled%2Famp_articleshow%2F108494832.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fex-pm-nawaz-sharifs-sons-arrest-warrants-in-panama-papers-scandal-linked-cases-cancelled%2Famp_articleshow%2F108494832.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Taken%20India%20For%20A%20Ride'%3A%20Why%20Supreme%20Court's%20Order%20Against%20Patanjali%20Is%20A%20Significant%20Step%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F09164656%2Framdev.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2027%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftaken-for-a-ride-sc-issues-contempt-notice-to-patanjali-ayurved-its-md-over-misleading-ads%5C%22%3E%20issued%20a%20contempt%20notice%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%2C%20the%20company%20founded%20by%20yoga%20guru%20Ramdev%2C%20and%20its%20managing%20director%20Acharya%20Balakrishna.%20This%20notice%20was%20in%20response%20to%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20continued%20dissemination%20of%20misleading%20advertisements%20claiming%20to%20offer%20permanent%20cures%20for%20various%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20bench%20consisting%20of%20Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20Ahsanuddin%20Amanullah%2C%20strongly%20criticised%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%20for%20its%20misleading%20advertising%20practices%20and%20temporarily%20banned%20the%20company%20from%20marketing%20its%20products%20until%20further%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20an%20assurance%20given%20to%20the%20court%20in%20November%202023%2C%20wherein%20the%20company%20promised%20not%20to%20release%20any%20statements%20that%20made%20unsubstantiated%20claims%20about%20medicinal%20efficacy%20or%20criticise%20any%20system%20of%20medicine%2C%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%20persisted%20in%20its%20misleading%20advertisements.%20The%20bench%20remarked%20that%20the%20entire%20nation%20had%20been%20deceived%20by%20these%20actions.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20also%20admonished%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20failing%20to%20take%20any%20action%20against%20these%20advertisements%20despite%20being%20aware%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20year%202022.%20In%20August%202022%2C%20the%20Indian%20Medical%20Association%20(IMA)%20took%20legal%20action%20in%20response%20to%20a%20Patanjali%20advertisement%20titled%20%E2%80%9CMisconceptions%20spread%20by%20allopathy%3A%20Save%20yourself%20and%20the%20country%20from%20the%20misconceptions%20spread%20by%20pharma%20and%20medical%20industry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20raised%20two%20main%20concerns%3A%20firstly%2C%20it%20accused%20Patanjali%20of%20consistently%20disseminating%20misinformation%20to%20denigrate%20allopathy%2C%20which%20it%20deemed%20as%20a%20deliberate%20and%20ongoing%20campaign.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20alleged%20that%20Patanjali%20was%20making%20exaggerated%20claims%20about%20the%20efficacy%20of%20its%20drugs%2C%20purportedly%20based%20on%20scientific%20evidence%2C%20which%20contradicted%20regulations%20banning%20such%20advertisements%20in%20the%20country.%20According%20to%20the%20IMA%2C%20these%20statements%20violated%20both%20the%20Drugs%20and%20Other%20Magical%20Remedies%20Act%2C%201954%20(DOMA)%20and%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%202019%20(CPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20Divya%20Amla%20Juice%2C%20recommended%20for%20individuals%20with%20diabetes%2C%20and%20Shivlingi%20Beej%20were%20deemed%20of%20%E2%80%98substandard%20quality%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20Ayurveda%20and%20Unani%20Office%20in%20Haridwar%2C%20as%20revealed%20in%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20drug%20regulator%20blacklisted%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20Divya%20Pharmacy%20for%20failing%20to%20adhere%20to%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20drug%20manufacturing%20standards.%20Additional%20reports%20have%20also%20raised%20concerns%20regarding%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20questionable%20quality%20control%20measures%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20robust%20clinical%20trial%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2021%2C%202023%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20comprising%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-patanjali-baba-ramdev-misleading-advertisements-indian-medical-association-242694%5C%22%3E%20Justices%20Ahsanuddin%20Amanullah%20and%20Prashant%20Kumar%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E%20cautioned%20Patanjali%20against%20advertising%20permanent%20cures%20and%20threatened%20to%20levy%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20each%20product%20making%20such%20claims.%20The%20court%20declined%20to%20engage%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CAllopathy%20v.%20Ayurveda%E2%80%9D%20discourse%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20assurances%20to%20the%20court%2C%20pledging%20no%20violation%20of%20laws%2C%20especially%20regarding%20product%20advertising%2C%20and%20refraining%20from%20making%20disparaging%20remarks%20about%20any%20medical%20system%2C%20Patanjali%20failed%20to%20uphold%20these%20commitments.%20Soon%20after%20the%20hearing%2C%20Baba%20Ramdev%20praised%20Patanjali%20products%20at%20a%20press%20conference%2C%20followed%20by%20advertisements%20appearing%20in%20mainstream%20media%20in%20December%202023%20and%20January%202024.%20These%20actions%20contravened%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20promise%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20strong%20dose%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20to%20enforce%20a%20ban%20on%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20advertisements%20marks%20a%20pivotal%20step%20in%20addressing%20the%20ongoing%20problem%20of%20misleading%20medical%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20society%20where%20many%20individuals%20lack%20sufficient%20knowledge%20of%20medical%20science%20and%20tend%20to%20place%20unwarranted%20faith%20in%20unverified%20herbal%20remedies%2C%20such%20advertising%20practices%20present%20a%20considerable%20risk.%20They%20propagate%20misinformation%20and%20may%20endorse%20products%20that%20could%20potentially%20pose%20harm%20to%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20efforts%20such%20as%20the%20collaboration%20between%20the%20Ministry%20of%20AYUSH%20and%20the%20Advertising%20Standards%20Council%20of%20India%20to%20tackle%20misleading%20advertisements%2C%20Patanjali%20continued%20to%20spread%20misinformation%20unchecked.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20signifies%20a%20crucial%20move%20towards%20protecting%20public%20health%20and%20ensuring%20accountability%20in%20the%20marketing%20of%20healthcare%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20persisted%20even%20when%20it%20was%20warned%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20early%20as%20November%202023%20to%20cease%20disseminating%20these%20assertions%20or%20risk%20substantial%20fines%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20each%20product%20featuring%20false%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20court%20reprimanded%20the%20government%20for%20its%20apparent%20negligence%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20turning%20a%20blind%20eye%20while%20the%20nation%20was%20deceived.%20The%20government%20could%20have%20legally%20compelled%20Patanjali%20to%20retract%20its%20advertisements%2C%20which%20flagrantly%20contravened%20Section%204%20of%20the%20Drugs%20and%20Other%20Magical%20Remedies%20Act%20(DOMA)%2C%201954%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20current%20legal%20framework%2C%20dissemination%20of%20misleading%20advertisements%20carries%20penalties.%20A%20first%20offence%20under%20the%20Drug%20and%20Magic%20Remedies%20(Objectionable%20Advertisements)%20Act%20(DOMA)%20could%20lead%20to%20imprisonment%20for%20six%20months%20and%2For%20a%20fine.%20For%20subsequent%20offences%2C%20the%20punishment%20may%20extend%20to%20one%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20imposes%20stricter%20consequences%2C%20with%20a%20potential%20imprisonment%20term%20of%20up%20to%20two%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20around%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20violations.%20Repeat%20offences%20escalate%20to%20a%20five-year%20imprisonment%20term%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20approximately%20Rs%2050%20lakh.%20The%20government%20has%20committed%20to%20investigating%20allegations%20and%20proposing%20appropriate%20actions.%20Strengthening%20advertising%20regulations%20for%20both%20Ayurvedic%20and%20over-the-counter%20(OTC)%20allopathic%20drugs%20should%20be%20a%20priority%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20operate%20in%20grey%20areas.%20For%20instance%2C%20DOMA%20does%20not%20recognise%20a%20list%20of%20drugs%20for%20which%20any%20advertisement%20is%20prohibited.%20But%20that%20still%20leaves%20the%20field%20dangerously%20open%20for%20all%20manner%20of%20products%2C%20including%20some%20vaccines.%20As%20for%20advertisements%20for%20ayurvedic%20products%2C%20these%20are%20more%20common%20than%20their%20allopathic%20counterparts%20because%20they%20do%20not%20require%20pre-approval%20or%20any%20stipulation%20of%20minimum%20information%20for%20the%20consumer.%20Indians%20who%20struggle%20with%20medical%20expenses%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20growing%20promotion%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cindigenous%E2%80%9D%20medical%20system%20supposedly%20offering%20cheaper%20