%22Akshay%20and%20Mahi%20have%20innovated%20nanocarbon%20for%20batteries%20from%20coconut%20shells.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FCancrie-1709646690.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FCancrie-1709646690-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FCancrie-1709646690-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FCancrie-1709646690-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FCancrie-1709646690-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-343985%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAkshay%20and%20Mahi%20have%20innovated%20nanocarbon%20for%20batteries%20from%20coconut%20shells.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EExtracting%20useful%20carbon%20from%20agri-waste%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkshay%20and%20Mahi%20grew%20up%20together%20studying%20in%20the%20same%20school%20in%20Jaipur.%20In%202010%2C%20Akshay%20went%20on%20to%20pursue%20PhD%20in%20chemical%20engineering%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20Mahi%20also%20went%20to%20Singapore%20to%20pursue%20her%20master%E2%80%99s%20at%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20during%20the%20same%20time%20that%20they%20started%20brainstorming%20about%20this%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%20this%20period%2C%20we%20tried%20to%20upcycle%20agricultural%20waste%20into%20fertilisers%2C%20low-cost%20fuels%2C%20and%20absorbents.%20After%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20of%20research%2C%20we%20achieved%20a%20major%20breakthrough%20by%20turning%20agri-waste%20into%20high-value%20nanocarbon%20for%20use%20in%20batteries.%20That%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20our%20project%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20A